{"sequence":106,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T21:45:05.095736621Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-bfa320c9","body":"finding_summary: The synthetic `br create` path always returns the hard-coded id `ms-e2e-scenario.task-follow-up-validation` (`src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs:36,339-374,490-503`). If code under test creates two follow-up beads or retries the create path after a partial failure, the fixture aliases both operations to the same bead instead of allocating a fresh id, which does not match real `br create` behavior.\naffected_files: src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs\nremediation_hint: Track a create counter and generate unique ids per created bead, or reject duplicate creates explicitly so tests cannot silently pass against aliased state.","dedup_key":"0e8eaa94fb2609d95a44144af3d1d71d39be78059961edb7ed51cc35b28add51","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417184955","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
